## Rules

### TEST-001: JUnit 5 Structure
severity: ERROR
scope: all JUnit 5 test classes
rule: All test methods MUST be annotated with `@Test` from JUnit 5 (`org.junit.jupiter`). Test class names MUST end with `Test`. Each test MUST have a `@DisplayName` annotation with a human-readable description.
threshold: min_coverage_pct=80, max_test_file_lines=400
example_correct: |
  @Test
  @DisplayName("should return error when order id is negative")
  void processOrder_NegativeId_ReturnsError() { ... }
example_incorrect: |
  @Test
  void test1() { ... }  // no display name — prohibited

### TEST-002: Mockito Usage
severity: ERROR
scope: all JUnit 5 unit tests using Mockito
rule: Mocks MUST be created with `@Mock` annotation and initialized with `MockitoExtension`. Inline `Mockito.mock()` calls in test methods are prohibited. `verify()` MUST be used to assert interactions on mocks.
threshold: min_coverage_pct=80
example_correct: |
  @ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
  class OrderServiceTest {
      @Mock private OrderRepository repo;
  }
example_incorrect: |
  void test() {
      OrderRepository repo = Mockito.mock(OrderRepository.class);  // inline — prohibited
  }
